ered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs William Austercarus was born about 1130, in Weekley, Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom. She married William Austercarus before 1145, in Europe. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"abt. 1130–":"umbes 1130–Surnud","1120–1145":"1120–1145","1145–1173":"1145–1173","1130–Female":"1130–Surnud","before 1145":"enne 1145","1145":"1145","1120":"1120","1130":"1130","1173":"1173","abt. 1130":"umbes 1130","Europe":"Europe","Weekley, Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom":"Weekley, Northamptonshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","of Weekley, Northants, England":"Weekley, Northamptonshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"abt. 1130–":"noin 1130–Kuollut","1120–1145":"1120–1145","1145–1173":"1145–1173","1130–Female":"1130–Kuollut","before 1145":"ennen vuotta 1145","1145":"1145","1120":"1120","1130":"1130","1173":"1173","abt. 1130":"noin 1130","Europe":"Europe","Weekley, Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom":"Weekley, Northamptonshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","of Weekley, Northants, England":"Weekley, Northamptonshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"abt. 1130–":"environ 1130–Décédée","1120–1145":"1120–1145","1145–1173":"1145–1173","1130–Female":"1130–Décédée","before 1145":"avant 1145","1145":"1145","1120":"1120","1130":"1130","1173":"1173","abt. 1130":"environ 1130","Europe":"Europe","Weekley, Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom":"Weekley, Northamptonshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","of Weekley, Northants, England":"Weekley, Northamptonshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Mrs William Austercarus est née environ 1130, à Weekley, Northamptonshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a épousé Willi